const faqItems = [
  {
    q: "What should Stratford-upon-Avon homeowners look for in a kitchen fitter?",
    a: "Stratford-upon-Avon's housing stock presents challenges that not every kitchen fitter is equipped to handle. The town centre contains timber-framed and Cotswold-edge period properties where walls are rarely square, floors have often settled unevenly over centuries, and ceiling heights can vary across a single room. Edwardian villas near the river bring their own considerations: high ceilings, original cornicing, and period architectural details that demand careful planning around. In Shottery and Tiddington, large detached properties carry high-value kitchens with island configurations, stone worktops, and full appliance suites — where finish quality matters enormously. For any of these property types, you need a fitter with deep experience of survey-led installation: someone who identifies the complications before the kitchen is ordered, not during the fit. Pindi Sahota has 30 years of experience working across Warwickshire's varied housing stock. He surveys every project personally, produces a fixed-price written quote, and does not proceed until every challenge in the room has been planned for.",
  },
  {
    q: "How much does kitchen fitting cost in Stratford-upon-Avon?",
    a: "Kitchen fitting costs in Stratford-upon-Avon vary according to the number of units, worktop material, appliance count, and the complexity of the room itself. Period properties in the town centre often involve additional preparation work — adjusting for uneven floors, accommodating irregular wall angles, or working around existing structural features — which is accounted for in the fixed-price quote following survey. As a general guide: a standard 10–15 unit kitchen with laminate worktops will typically fall in the range of £1,200–£2,000 for fitting labour; a larger installation of 18–22 units with stone worktops and integrated appliances will typically range from £2,200–£3,500; complex projects with islands, full-height larder towers, or significant preparation work will sit above this. All prices are confirmed as fixed, itemised quotes following Pindi's pre-installation survey. There are no estimates and no retrospective charges.",
  },
  {
    q: "Do you cover CV37?",
    a: "Yes. Pindi covers the whole of the CV37 postcode area, which encompasses Stratford-upon-Avon town centre and the surrounding villages including Shottery, Tiddington, Bishopton, and Bridgetown. He also regularly covers nearby areas including Wellesbourne, Alcester, and Henley-in-Arden. He is based at 242 Hollyfast Road, Coundon, Coventry CV6 2AH — approximately 20 miles north of Stratford — and serves south Warwickshire as a regular part of his working area. Call 07399 651836 to confirm coverage for your specific address.",
  },
  {
    q: "How long does installation take in a period Stratford property?",
    a: "Installation timescales in Stratford's period properties are generally longer than a straightforward modern kitchen of equivalent unit count. Where a modern room with square walls and level floors might take three to four days for a 15-unit kitchen, the same kitchen in a timber-framed or Edwardian property may require an additional day or more to level base units correctly, scribe units to uneven walls, and accommodate ceiling height variations. A larger installation in one of Shottery's or Tiddington's detached properties — 18–22 units with an island, stone worktops, and integrated appliances — will typically take five to eight working days, and potentially longer if the room requires significant preparation. Pindi gives a realistic duration estimate during the pre-installation survey, based on the specific room and kitchen specification. This allows you to plan around the work accurately.",
  },
  {
    q: "Which retailers do you fit in Stratford-upon-Avon?",
    a: "Pindi fits kitchens from all retailers and manufacturers, regardless of price point. Because he is fully independent — not employed by or tied to any kitchen retailer — he can work with any brand and advise you without conflict of interest. In Stratford-upon-Avon, common brands he installs include Wren Kitchens, Howdens, Magnet, Kutchenhaus, Mereway, Neptune, and deVOL (the latter two particularly suited to Stratford's period properties), as well as Häcker and Nobilia for a contemporary German finish. He also fits from IKEA, Wickes, B&Q, Benchmarx, DIY Kitchens, Symphony, and Masterclass. If your kitchen is from a brand not listed here, call 07399 651836 — in almost every case it can be accommodated.",
  },
];

const internalLinks = [
  {
    label: "Book a pre-installation survey",
    href: "/survey/",
    description: "£195 survey credited back in full when you proceed — the essential first step",
  },
  {
    label: "Kitchen fitting costs explained",
    href: "/costs/",
    description: "Fully itemised guide to what affects kitchen installation prices",
  },
