    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 1: Independent vs Retailer Fitters -->
  <section class="section" style="background: var(--bg-light);">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="max-w-3xl fade-up">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--navy);">
          Independent Kitchen Fitter vs Retailer Fitter — Why It Matters More in Stratford
        </h2>
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          For a straightforward modern kitchen in a box-fresh new build, the choice between an independent fitter and a retailer's installation scheme may be less critical. For a kitchen in a Stratford-upon-Avon period property — where walls are rarely plumb, floors may have settled unevenly over two centuries, and room shapes resist standard unit configurations — the difference is substantial.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          Retailer-scheme fitters work to a pace determined by the retailer's margin rather than your room's requirements. An independent fitter like Pindi Sahota works directly for you, with the time and flexibility to scribe units to an uneven wall, re-level a base run across a sloping original floor, and resolve each complication as it arises — at no additional charge, because the survey identified it in advance.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          Independence also means impartiality. Pindi is not employed by or tied to any retailer, which means he can give you an honest assessment of the practicalities — what installs well in a period room, what requires additional preparation, what to watch for with specific brands or finishes — without any commercial interest in the answer.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          For Stratford homeowners investing in a premium kitchen in a characterful property, an independent fitter with deep experience of the area's housing stock is the surest path to a result that matches the investment.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
