          Pindi Sahota has been fitting kitchens across Warwickshire for 30 years and understands the county's varied property character in detail. He is based at 242 Hollyfast Road, Coundon, Coventry CV6 2AH — approximately 20 miles north of Stratford — and covers CV37 and the surrounding area as a regular part of his working territory.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          Stratford-upon-Avon's housing stock is more varied — and more technically demanding — than most Warwickshire towns. In the town centre, timber-framed and Cotswold-edge period properties date back centuries: their kitchen rooms present irregular shapes, low or varying ceiling heights, walls that are neither square nor plumb, and original floor levels that require careful management before a single unit can be set out. Getting this right demands a fitter who surveys the room before the kitchen is ordered, not one who arrives on day one with a standard plan and attempts to fit units to a room that was never designed for them.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          The Edwardian villas along the river and in the roads running towards Shottery bring high ceilings, wide room proportions, and often substantial kitchen footprints — well suited to full-height larder towers, island configurations, and premium appliance suites. Property values in Stratford are among the highest in Warwickshire, and homeowners in these properties invest accordingly, expecting a finish to match.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          In Shottery and Tiddington, large detached homes carry the modern open-plan kitchen-diner-living format common across south Warwickshire's executive housing: larger unit counts, quartz or granite worktops, integrated appliances throughout, and often an island that becomes the focal point of the room. On the modern developments south of town along the A3400 corridor, new-build kitchens demand precision and speed. Pindi has the experience to deliver across all of these contexts.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

