          Every kitchen fitting project begins with a pre-installation survey, carried out by Pindi personally. The survey costs £195 and is credited back in full if you proceed with the installation. In Stratford-upon-Avon, this survey is not a formality — it is genuinely essential. Period properties in particular contain variables that cannot be assessed from a floor plan: a wall that looks straight on paper but has a 30mm bow across its run; a floor that drops 15mm from one end of the kitchen to the other; a ceiling that is lower over the window alcove than the rest of the room.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          During the survey, Pindi takes precise room measurements, checks ceiling heights and wall angles throughout — not just at one point — inspects existing plumbing and electrics routes, reviews your kitchen plan and elevation drawings in detail, and identifies any work that needs to happen before or alongside the installation. For Stratford's older properties, this often includes discussion of floor levelling, structural wall considerations, and whether any specialist work is needed before units can be set out.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: var(--text-soft);">
          After the survey you receive a written, fixed-price quote. The price does not change unless you change the scope of work. There are no estimates and no retrospective charges for complications that should have been identified in advance.
        </p>
